The paper discusses Rush Hour Logic as a model of computation, which suggests it could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of boolean circuits and memory also suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The mention of parking lot configurations and maze puzzles suggests a connection to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
